          <div class="page-header-content">
            <span class="page-header-badge"><i class="bi bi-question-circle-fill"></i> FAQ</span>
            <h1 data-i18n="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <p class="page-header-desc" data-i18n="faq-subtitle">
              Find answers to common questions about government services
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="faq-container">
            <!-- FAQ Category: General -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-info-circle-fill"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-general">General Questions</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-what-are-the-office-hours-of-the-municipal-hall">
                    What are the office hours of the Provincial Capitol?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-the-municipal-hall-is-open-monday-to-friday-800">
                      The Provincial Capitol is open Monday to Friday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM, with a lunch
                      break from 12:00 PM to 1:00 PM. We are closed on weekends and national/local
                      holidays.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-how-can-i-contact-a-specific-municipal-office">
                    How can I contact a specific provincial office?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>
                      Visit our
                      <a href="../government/" data-i18n="faq-government-directory"
                        >Government Directory</a
                      >
                      page to find contact information for all provincial offices and department
                      heads.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-can-i-request-services-online">
                    Can I request services online?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-currently-most-services-require-inperson">
                      Currently, most services require in-person applications. However, we are
                      working on implementing online services for select transactions. Check
                      individual service pages for updates.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: Certificates -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-file-earmark-text-fill"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-certificates">Certificates & Documents</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-how-long-does-it-take-to-get-a-birth-certificate">
                    How long does it take to get a birth certificate?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-for-birth-certificates-registered-in-camnorte-it">
                      For birth certificates registered in Camarines Norte, it typically takes 15-30 minutes
                      while you wait, provided the record is readily available.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-can-someone-else-request-my-certificate-for-me">
                    Can someone else request my certificate for me?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-yes-but-they-must-bring">Yes, but they must bring:</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-an-authorization-letter-signed-by-you">
                        An authorization letter signed by you
                      </li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-valid-id-of-both-you-and-the-representative">
                        Valid ID of both you and the representative
                      </li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-photocopy-of-your-valid-id">Photocopy of your valid ID</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-what-is-the-difference-between-psa-and-local">
                    What is the difference between PSA and local civil registrar certificates?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-both-are-certified-true-copies-psa-certificates">
                      Both are certified true copies. PSA certificates are the nationally-recognized
                      version required for passport and visa applications. Local civil registrar
                      certificates are accepted for most local transactions and are often processed
                      faster.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: Business -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-shop"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-business">Business & Permits</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-when-should-i-renew-my-business-permit">
                    When should I renew my business permit?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-business-permits-must-be-renewed-annually">
                      Business permits must be renewed annually, preferably in January. The deadline
                      for penalty-free renewal is typically January 20th of each year.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-what-do-i-need-to-start-a-new-business-in-camnorte">
                    What do I need to start a new business in Camarines Norte?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-to-start-a-new-business-youll-need">
                      To start a new business, you'll need:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-dti-registration-for-sole-proprietorship-or-sec">
                        DTI Registration (for sole proprietorship) or SEC Registration (for
                        corporation)
                      </li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-barangay-clearance">Barangay Clearance</li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-community-tax-certificate-cedula">
                        Community Tax Certificate (Cedula)
                      </li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-location-sketchmap">Location Sketch/Map</li>
                      <li>Contract of Lease (if renting)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                      See the official
                      <a
                        href="https://camsnorte.com/citizens-charter/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-business-permit-page"
                        >Citizen's Charter</a
                      >
                      for complete details.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: Payments -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-cash-coin"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-payments">Payments & Fees</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-what-payment-methods-are-accepted">
                    What payment methods are accepted?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-currently-we-accept-cash-payments-at-the">
                      Currently, we accept cash payments at the Provincial Treasurer's Office. We are
                      working on implementing online payment options for taxes and fees.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-how-can-i-pay-my-real-property-tax">
                    How can I pay my real property tax?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-visit-the-municipal-treasurers-office-at-the">
                      Visit the Provincial Treasurer's Office at the Provincial Capitol with your Tax
                      Declaration or latest Official Receipt. Payment is in cash. Property taxes are
                      due quarterly, but you may pay annually to avail of discounts.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: Social Services -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-people-fill"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-social">Social Services</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-how-do-i-apply-for-a-senior-citizen-id">
                    How do I apply for a Senior Citizen ID?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-go-to-the-municipal-social-welfare-and">
                      Go to the Provincial Social Welfare and Development Office (MSWDO) with:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-birth-certificate-or-any-valid-id-showing-your">
                        Birth Certificate or any valid ID showing your age (60 and above)
                      </li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-1x1-id-photo">1x1 ID photo</li>
                      <li data-i18n="faq-barangay-residence-certificate">
                        Barangay Residence Certificate
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p data-i18n="faq-the-id-is-issued-for-free">The ID is issued for free.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-what-benefits-do-senior-citizens-receive">
                    What benefits do senior citizens receive?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-senior-citizens-enjoy-20-discount-and-vat">
                      Senior citizens enjoy 20% discount and VAT exemption on purchases (with a
                      minimum purchase amount per establishment), priority lanes, and access to
                      special programs and medical assistance from the municipality.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: Technical -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-gear-fill"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-technical">Technical Questions</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-i-found-a-broken-link-or-error-on-this-website">
                    I found a broken link or error on this website. How do I report it?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>
                      Thank you for helping us improve! Please send us message at
                      <a
                        href="mailto:volunteer@bettercamnorte.org"
                        data-i18n="faq-volunteerbettercamnorteorg"
                        >volunteer@bettercamnorte.org</a
                      >
                      and write "Website Issue" as the subject. Describe the problem and include the
                      page URL if possible.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-is-this-website-mobilefriendly">
                    Is this website mobile-friendly?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p data-i18n="faq-yes-better-camnorte-is-fully-responsive-and">
                      Yes! BetterCamNorte is fully responsive and optimized for mobile phones,
                      tablets, and desktop computers.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Category: About -->
            <div class="faq-category">
              <div class="faq-category-header">
                <i class="bi bi-person-badge-fill"></i>
                <h2 data-i18n="faq-about-the-developer">About the Developer</h2>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-list">
                <details class="faq-accordion">
                  <summary data-i18n="faq-who-developed-better-camnorte">
                    Who developed BetterCamNorte?
                  </summary>
                  <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>
                      <a
                        href="https://ramonloganjr.com/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-ramon-logan-jr"
                        >Ramon Logan Jr.</a
                      >
                      is the developer behind
                      <a
                        href="https://abakada.org"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-abakadaorg"
                        >Abakada.org</a
                      >
                      and BetterCamNorte, a community-driven initiative building a digital bridge
                      between the residents of Camarines Norte and the local government of Camarines Norte. Based in
                      the United Arab Emirates, he works in IT and practices full-stack development,
                      helping build practical digital solutions in web development, design, cloud
                      services, and cybersecurity.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      He also started
                      <a
                        href="https://hellopinas.com"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-hellopinascom"
                        >HelloPinas.com</a
                      >, a small cloud-based solutions initiative. Ramon contributes to
                      <a
                        href="https://bettergov.ph"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-bettergovph"
                        >BetterGov.ph</a
                      >, a volunteer-driven civic-tech effort focused on improving access to local
                      government information and services in the Philippines.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      He is also an individual participant of the
                      <a
                        href="https://openjsf.org/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        data-i18n="faq-openjs-foundation"
                        >OpenJS Foundation</a
                      >, a nonprofit supporting open-source JavaScript communities worldwide.
                    </p>
                    <p data-i18n="faq-ramon-has-made-the-camnorte-project-open-source">
                      Ramon has made the Camarines Norte Project open source under MIT | CC BY 4.0 to empower
                      community-driven development, and contributions are warmly welcomed from
                      everyone; whether you are a developer, data researcher, designer, content
                      writer, translator, or a concerned citizen of Camarines Norte, your participation helps
                      shape the project for all.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Still Have Questions -->
            <div class="faq-cta">
              <i class="bi bi-chat-dots-fill"></i>
              <div class="faq-cta-content">
                <h3 data-i18n="faq-still-questions">Still have questions?</h3>
                <p data-i18n="faq-contact-help">
                  If you didn't find the answer you were looking for, please don't hesitate to
                  contact us.
                </p>
              </div>
              <a href="../contact/" class="btn btn-primary" data-i18n="faq-contact-us"
                >Contact Us</a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
